verbose_text: On the Pds5 spine many Pds5 amino acid side chains are in contact with the Scc1 peptide, as shown and listed in XREF_FIG D. Substitution by lysine of the residue equivalent to LtY493 in S. cerevisiae, namely, Y458K, greatly reduced proliferation and caused temperature sensitive lethality (XREF_FIG A, right, and XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY).
